霍齐尔谈 LGB 和跨性别群体被视为“替罪羊” https://www.nme.com/news/music/hozier-on-the-lgbtq-trans-community-being-targeted-as-scapegoats-3486053?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=hozier-on-the-lgbtq-跨社区成为替罪羊Liberty DunworthMon, 21 Aug 2023 14:45:14 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndiePophttps://www.nme.com/?p=3486053 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="霍齐尔于 2023 年 7 月 21 日在英国伦敦亚历山德拉宫公园演出。" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “我认为 LGBTQ+ 群体，尤其是跨性别群体越来越多地见证了这一点”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hozier-on-the-lgbtq-trans-community-being-targeted-as-scapegoats-3486053">Hozier 发表的有关 LGB 和跨性别群体被视为“替罪羊”的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="霍齐尔于 2023 年 7 月 21 日在英国伦敦亚历山德拉宫公园演出。" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/hozier">霍齐尔</a>反思了全球当前的政治和社会气候，并表示他认为 LGBTQ+ 群体正成为替罪羊。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/hozier-there-has-always-been-a-space-in-my-work-for-my-own-conscience-3484983">霍齐尔：“我的作品中始终为我自己的良心留有空间”</a><br /></strong></li></ul><p>这一讨论是在上周（8 月 19 日） <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/hozier-there-has-always-been-a-space-in-my-work-for-my-own-conscience-3484983">接受<em>NME</em>的一次新采访</a>时进行的，在采访中，这位爱尔兰创作歌手公开了他的音乐背后的灵感——尤其是他的新专辑<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/hozier-unreal-unearth-review-epic-expansive-and-ethereal-3483924">《Unreal Unearth》。</a></p><p> Hozier（真名 Andrew Hozier-Byrne）在接受<em>NME</em>的 Nick Levine 采访时，谈到了 LGBTQ+ 群体成员普遍面临的强烈反对和偏见，以及他们在困难时期越来越多地被用作“替罪羊”的情况。</p><p>当被问及他对 LGBTQ+ 群体的长期支持，以及为什么他如此愿意毫不犹豫地反对压迫态度时，霍齐尔说：“我发现这是一个很难以某种简洁、明确的方式解决的问题。</p><p> “但我认为你至少应该尝试诚实，这就是我在工作中尝试做的事情。在我的作品中，我始终有自己的良心以及我对我们所生活的共同社会的责任的看法。</p><p> “此外，我敏锐地意识到——而且越来越意识到——当事情变得困难时，总有一部分人面临成为替罪羊的风险。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="霍齐尔谈新专辑“Unreal Unearth”、热门单曲“Take Me To Church”并维护自己的隐私" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-HlEYnU8n7g?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>他继续解释说，他认为社区面临的许多强烈反对源于政府无法为困难的情况提供“简单的答案”，并且倾向于将焦点转移到少数群体身上。</p><p> “对于他们面临的巨大问题，政治领导人没有简单的答案，甚至很难找到答案，而对于我们所有人都面临的系统方面的困难挑战来说，这些答案往往更为重要，因为它们让我们集体失败，”他补充道。</p><p> “所以通常最简单的事情就是跳上文化战争问题，跳上替罪羊[并]煽动一些恐慌。而那个社会中的少数群体总是最先成为目标，”霍齐尔继续说道。 “我认为 LGBTQ+ 群体，尤其是跨性别群体越来越多地见证了这一点。”</p><p> Elsewhere in the interview, <em>NME</em> also highlighted how Hozier openly showed his support for LGBTQ+ rights with his 2013 breakout single &#39;Take Me To Church&#39; – which was partly inspired by the hypocrisy of the Catholic Church – and again in 2020, when he used his social media channels to reaffirm his stance during Pride Month. </p><figure id="attachment_3484665" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3484665" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3484665" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing.jpg" alt="Hozier performs on day 3 of the 10th Anniversary of Shaky Knees 2023 at Central Park on May 07, 2023 in Atlanta, Georgia. Credit: Scott Legato/Getty" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hozier-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3484665" class="wp-caption-text"> Hozier performs on day 3 of the 10th Anniversary of Shaky Knees 2023 at Central Park on May 07, 2023 in Atlanta, Georgia. Credit: Scott Legato/Getty</figcaption></figure><p> “Trans rights are human rights,”<a href="https://twitter.com/Hozier/status/1269636511265435648?s=20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">he wrote on Twitter</a> (now X). “I don&#39;t know who might need to hear this today but you are loved, you are seen and you deserve to be happy and respected for who you are and the God given life you live.”</p><p> Last Thursday (August 17), <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/hozier-unreal-unearth-review-epic-expansive-and-ethereal-3483924"><em>NME</em> gave the songwriter&#39;s new album a four-star review</a> , and described his third LP as “epic, expansive and ethereal”.</p><p> “&#39;Unreal Unearth&#39; traverses a variety of styles from softer piano ballads like &#39;Butchered Tongue&#39; to up-tempo folk-pop &#39;Anything But&#39; and fuzzy-guitar rock stomp &#39;Francesca&#39;,” it read.</p><p> “Hozier not only navigates different genres on &#39;Unreal Unearth,&#39; but chooses between moments of sparseness […] while also making space for expansive tracks,” it adds. “It sounds like a movie score, complete with swelling strings and haunting distorted vocals.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hozier-on-the-lgbtq-trans-community-being-targeted-as-scapegoats-3486053">Hozier on the LGB and trans community being targeted as “scapegoats”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
